t1919.text: Then when March 2015 rolled around and I bought myself an Xbox One the first game I bought for it (outside of what was bundled with the console) was TF1. I think, next to R6 Siege, it might still be my most played game on XB1.

t1920.text: The game came out a day after my birthday on March 13th so I went down to EB Games after school and picked up a PC copy, The Art of Titanfall and two shirts. TF1 was the last FPS I played seriously and was actually good at on PC. Christmas that year I got a 360 copy as well.

t1921.text: I have no idea how many hours I've put into both games. I played the original TF1 beta on PC in January(?) 2014 as much as I humanly could and the two maps you could play on, Angel City and Fracture, are still my favourite maps to this day.

t1922.text: While I still enjoyed TF2's maps to an extent I still think TF1's maps were all better so I honestly have the most fun in TF2 on the 3 TF1 maps they brought in: Angel City, Rise and War Games, which happen to be 3 of some of my favourite TF1 maps so there ya go
